20
00:01:39,580 --> 00:01:42,980
=A Date With The Future=

21
00:01:43,470 --> 00:01:45,980
=Episode 26=
(Do What You Want. I'm Here For You)

22
00:02:00,688 --> 00:02:01,688
(Remember to take your meals on time.)

23
00:02:02,767 --> 00:02:03,847
(I'll be worried)

24
00:02:04,248 --> 00:02:05,287
(if your gastric issue acts up again.)

25
00:02:35,168 --> 00:02:35,848
(All right.)

26
00:02:37,967 --> 00:02:39,568
Let's eat together when we both have time.

27
00:02:47,207 --> 00:02:47,687
(Let's eat together)

28
00:02:47,927 --> 00:02:48,568
(when we both have time.)

29
00:03:11,886 --> 00:03:12,608
Captain Jin.

30
00:03:15,647 --> 00:03:16,767
You looked fine in the afternoon.

31
00:03:17,448 --> 00:03:19,367
Why the long face?

32
00:03:21,448 --> 00:03:22,207
Zang Qiu hasn't replied to my text

33
00:03:22,207 --> 00:03:23,087
for a long while.

34
00:03:33,527 --> 00:03:34,448
She's a doctor.

35
00:03:35,888 --> 00:03:36,807
She has to perform surgeries

36
00:03:36,888 --> 00:03:38,527
for several hours.

37
00:03:39,247 --> 00:03:40,848
It's normal that she doesn't
reply to your text.

38
00:03:41,207 --> 00:03:41,848
Was she like this too

39
00:03:41,927 --> 00:03:43,207
when she was with Fang Huai?

40
00:03:45,448 --> 00:03:46,168
Why?

41
00:03:47,487 --> 00:03:49,448
I'm just curious.

42
00:03:50,888 --> 00:03:52,128
Sometimes,

43
00:03:53,367 --> 00:03:55,967
I feel that Dr. Zang doesn't really like me.

44
00:03:57,408 --> 00:03:59,328
But sometimes I could feel something from her.

45
00:04:02,008 --> 00:04:02,608
Captain Jin.

46
00:04:03,207 --> 00:04:04,367
Can you tell me about Fang Huai?

47
00:04:10,008 --> 00:04:10,967
Fang Huai

48
00:04:13,288 --> 00:04:14,848
was like the sun.

49
00:04:16,848 --> 00:04:18,127
He brought happiness

50
00:04:19,648 --> 00:04:20,968
to everyone around him.

51
00:04:23,927 --> 00:04:25,567
Speaking of which, both of you
share this in common.

52
00:04:27,487 --> 00:04:28,327
Does Dr. Zang see me

53
00:04:28,408 --> 00:04:29,687
as Fang Huai's replacement?

54
00:04:30,927 --> 00:04:31,687
No, it won't be.

55
00:04:32,608 --> 00:04:33,687
Though you're similar,

56
00:04:34,487 --> 00:04:36,127
there's something different between you two.

57
00:04:37,007 --> 00:04:39,007
He was like the rising sun
in the morning.

58
00:04:40,608 --> 00:04:41,447
Bright

59
00:04:43,408 --> 00:04:44,247
and lively.

60
00:04:45,608 --> 00:04:49,367
While you are the sun after the rain

61
00:04:50,608 --> 00:04:51,687
that brings warmth to everyone.

62
00:04:54,728 --> 00:04:56,367
But the sun that appears in the morning

63
00:04:56,807 --> 00:04:57,927
is there every day,

64
00:05:00,487 --> 00:05:01,408
unlike the sun after the rain,

65
00:05:02,088 --> 00:05:03,447
which isn't always present.

66
00:05:06,088 --> 00:05:07,048
But life

67
00:05:09,447 --> 00:05:11,168
isn't sunny all the time.

68
00:05:12,687 --> 00:05:13,648
And that makes the sun after the rain

69
00:05:14,687 --> 00:05:15,968
even more precious.

70
00:05:19,848 --> 00:05:20,648
I get you.

71
00:05:21,487 --> 00:05:23,127
I want to be that sun for Zang Qiu，

72
00:05:23,567 --> 00:05:24,447
warming her up

73
00:05:24,927 --> 00:05:26,687
and leading her out of the gloom.

74
00:05:30,408 --> 00:05:30,807
Let's go.

75
00:05:54,247 --> 00:05:54,728
Careful.

76
00:05:56,168 --> 00:05:56,648
Slowly.

77
00:05:59,447 --> 00:06:01,288
This is Xu Lai of Huaigang TV Station,

78
00:06:01,367 --> 00:06:02,927
reporting live from the fire scene

79
00:06:03,007 --> 00:06:03,848
at Nanxiang Nursing Home.

80
00:06:29,447 --> 00:06:29,927
Hello.

81
00:06:30,288 --> 00:06:31,408
We're the reporters from the TV station

82
00:06:31,528 --> 00:06:32,807
and would like to interview you.

83
00:06:32,927 --> 00:06:34,088
Was there only one

84
00:06:34,208 --> 00:06:35,327
with critical injury at the scene?

85
00:06:35,528 --> 00:06:36,768
I was sleeping

86
00:06:36,768 --> 00:06:38,007
and didn't know what was going on.

87
00:06:38,007 --> 00:06:38,887
The fire just broke out.

88
00:06:39,088 --> 00:06:39,807
Right.

89
00:06:40,007 --> 00:06:41,048
It was dark outside.

90
00:06:41,088 --> 00:06:42,408
I didn't see anything.

91
00:06:42,848 --> 00:06:43,408
I know something.

92
00:06:43,408 --> 00:06:44,687
My room is next to hers.

93
00:06:45,168 --> 00:06:46,168
Everyone, hush.

94
00:06:47,487 --> 00:06:48,048
That's right.

95
00:06:48,327 --> 00:06:48,927
The nursing home

96
00:06:49,127 --> 00:06:50,848
evacuated all the elderly
in time.

97
00:06:51,447 --> 00:06:52,768
But one elderly lady

98
00:06:53,007 --> 00:06:54,127
couldn't escape in time

99
00:06:54,367 --> 00:06:55,887
because she has difficulty walking.

100
00:06:56,288 --> 00:06:58,247
That's why she was trapped in the fire.

101
00:06:58,968 --> 00:06:59,887
Are you the person in charge

102
00:06:59,887 --> 00:07:00,728
of the nursing home?

103
00:07:01,728 --> 00:07:04,528
I'm the director of Nanxiang Nursing Home.

104
00:07:06,088 --> 00:07:08,567
Why did the elderly lady have no caregivers?

105
00:07:08,648 --> 00:07:09,968
Since you knew
that she can't walk well,

106
00:07:10,048 --> 00:07:11,927
why wasn't she rescued from the fire immediately?

107
00:07:12,927 --> 00:07:14,687
The situation was chaotic

108
00:07:14,887 --> 00:07:16,168
and the fire was intense.

109
00:07:16,367 --> 00:07:17,528
We have limited hands.

110
00:07:17,687 --> 00:07:18,968
So, it's possible
that one or two

111
00:07:19,007 --> 00:07:19,487
would be left out.

112
00:07:19,728 --> 00:07:20,528
Left out?

113
00:07:21,408 --> 00:07:22,367
Is this the attitude of the nursing home

114
00:07:22,408 --> 00:07:23,848
towards this fire incident?

115
00:07:27,848 --> 00:07:29,247
That Ms. Zheng mentioned

116
00:07:29,807 --> 00:07:31,487
was abandoned by her son

117
00:07:31,487 --> 00:07:32,487
in the nursing home.

118
00:07:33,247 --> 00:07:34,007
It has been three or four years.

119
00:07:34,288 --> 00:07:36,327
And her son never visited her.

120
00:07:36,648 --> 00:07:38,528
Because of this, she's upset

121
00:07:38,728 --> 00:07:40,367
and has even attempted

122
00:07:40,807 --> 00:07:41,687
to kill herself.

123
00:07:43,007 --> 00:07:46,208
This fire is quite suspicious.

124
00:07:46,687 --> 00:07:48,487
She's the only one severely injured.

125
00:07:48,848 --> 00:07:50,168
I suspect

126
00:07:50,848 --> 00:07:51,608
that it was Ms. Zheng

127
00:07:51,687 --> 00:07:52,608
who started the fire.

128
00:07:54,288 --> 00:07:55,447
Are you suggesting

129
00:07:55,768 --> 00:07:57,327
that she wanted to commit suicide?

130
00:07:57,487 --> 00:07:59,048
Last time, she even said
that she wanted to set a fire

131
00:07:59,088 --> 00:08:00,127
to kill herself.

132
00:08:04,848 --> 00:08:05,408
Hello.

133
00:08:05,968 --> 00:08:06,687
May I ask...

134
00:08:09,528 --> 00:08:10,528
The cause of the fire

135
00:08:11,168 --> 00:08:12,807
is still unclear.

136
00:08:13,007 --> 00:08:13,608
The nursing home

137
00:08:13,807 --> 00:08:15,728
has also suffered significant damage.

138
00:08:16,487 --> 00:08:18,687
If this incident is caused
by someone's action

139
00:08:18,848 --> 00:08:20,367
and brought inconvenience
to other elderly people,

140
00:08:20,807 --> 00:08:22,608
we'll hold them accountable.

141
00:08:23,327 --> 00:08:24,208
Please rest assured.

142
00:08:24,447 --> 00:08:26,288
As the director,

143
00:08:26,487 --> 00:08:27,728
I'll take responsibility
and get them safe

144
00:08:27,927 --> 00:08:28,728
no matter what.

145
00:08:29,007 --> 00:08:31,687
Hopefully, everyone

146
00:08:31,887 --> 00:08:33,847
could give us concerns and support.

147
00:08:43,048 --> 00:08:44,528
Jin Shichuan, how are you?

148
00:08:44,927 --> 00:08:45,607
Did you get injured?

149
00:08:46,248 --> 00:08:46,727
No.

150
00:08:47,368 --> 00:08:47,768
By the way,

151
00:08:48,128 --> 00:08:48,967
how's the situation inside?

152
00:08:49,288 --> 00:08:50,087
The director responded

153
00:08:50,128 --> 00:08:51,207
that the elderly lady started the fire.

154
00:08:51,408 --> 00:08:51,888
What do you think?

155
00:08:52,447 --> 00:08:54,368
I can't answer you as of now.

156
00:08:55,327 --> 00:08:56,327
We have to wait for
the fire investigation department

157
00:08:56,327 --> 00:08:58,248
to examine the scene

158
00:08:59,408 --> 00:09:00,488
and identify the origin point

159
00:09:01,168 --> 00:09:03,128
before we analyze the fire incident.

160
00:09:05,368 --> 00:09:07,008
But based on what happened earlier,

161
00:09:07,288 --> 00:09:08,128
I don't think

162
00:09:08,207 --> 00:09:09,528
it was the elderly lady
who started the fire.

163
00:09:09,727 --> 00:09:10,648
Why?

164
00:09:10,888 --> 00:09:12,528
I saved her just now.

165
00:09:13,008 --> 00:09:14,128
When I found her,

166
00:09:14,128 --> 00:09:15,648
she was crawling into the corridor

167
00:09:16,087 --> 00:09:17,607
and she had some simple
protection on her.

168
00:09:18,447 --> 00:09:20,128
She had a strong will to live.

169
00:09:20,327 --> 00:09:21,967
I don't think she wanted
to kill herself.

170
00:09:23,528 --> 00:09:25,288
The director acted weird too.

171
00:09:25,768 --> 00:09:26,528
I'm thinking of digging deep.

172
00:09:26,927 --> 00:09:28,888
Go ahead and do what you want.

173
00:09:29,288 --> 00:09:30,207
I'm here for you.

174
00:09:30,567 --> 00:09:31,327
I'll support you.

175
00:09:31,847 --> 00:09:33,207
Step back. It's dangerous.

176
00:09:33,447 --> 00:09:34,087
Be careful.

177
00:09:34,327 --> 00:09:34,607
I will.

178
00:09:34,888 --> 00:09:35,528
Raise the hose higher.

179
00:09:35,567 --> 00:09:36,168
Higher.

180
00:09:36,207 --> 00:09:37,327
Up there.

181
00:09:40,130 --> 00:09:44,060
(Brave Dangers and Serve the People)

182
00:09:44,488 --> 00:09:45,528
I interviewed the people involved

183
00:09:45,687 --> 00:09:46,727
these two days.

184
00:09:47,847 --> 00:09:48,447
Also,

185
00:09:48,447 --> 00:09:49,327
these are the photos

186
00:09:49,368 --> 00:09:50,048
I took at the scene.

187
00:09:50,128 --> 00:09:51,048
But I couldn't go in deeper

188
00:09:51,087 --> 00:09:51,847
the fire scene.

189
00:09:52,128 --> 00:09:53,488
I couldn't know the situation inside.

190
00:09:54,048 --> 00:09:55,327
It's fine. I was there.

191
00:09:55,368 --> 00:09:56,447
I can work this out with you.

192
00:10:08,567 --> 00:10:09,567
Look at the wall here.

193
00:10:10,327 --> 00:10:12,368
There are bulges on the wall.

194
00:10:13,408 --> 00:10:15,048
Maybe they used other materials
for expansion

195
00:10:15,087 --> 00:10:16,488
after the construction is done.

196
00:10:23,008 --> 00:10:24,008
I guess this is the partition

197
00:10:24,008 --> 00:10:25,368
used to separate rooms.

198
00:10:28,368 --> 00:10:28,927
I remember

199
00:10:29,008 --> 00:10:30,368
I have seen many small rooms

200
00:10:31,607 --> 00:10:33,567
divided from a big room

201
00:10:33,768 --> 00:10:35,248
when I was there.

202
00:10:35,967 --> 00:10:37,368
The internal structure is very complex.

203
00:10:37,967 --> 00:10:39,847
Many emergency exits were blocked.

204
00:10:40,207 --> 00:10:41,048
It seems that Wang Yi

205
00:10:41,128 --> 00:10:42,168
has illegally expanded

206
00:10:42,288 --> 00:10:43,567
the nursing home

207
00:10:43,687 --> 00:10:44,927
for more accommodation.

208
00:10:47,370 --> 00:10:52,490
(Xin'an Apartment)

209
00:10:53,408 --> 00:10:54,408
Granny, let me help you.

210
00:10:55,008 --> 00:10:55,847
Thank you.

211
00:10:56,607 --> 00:10:57,967
The room is damp

212
00:10:58,248 --> 00:11:00,288
and the bedsheets are moldy.

213
00:11:04,648 --> 00:11:05,248
Granny.

214
00:11:05,768 --> 00:11:07,128
Didn't you stay

215
00:11:07,128 --> 00:11:08,168
in the nursing home before?

216
00:11:10,128 --> 00:11:11,528
That's a private nursing home.

217
00:11:11,888 --> 00:11:13,008
What can we expect from them?

218
00:11:13,528 --> 00:11:14,567
They always mistreat and
neglect people like us

219
00:11:14,687 --> 00:11:16,807
who have no children.

220
00:11:17,607 --> 00:11:19,288
The temporary shelter

221
00:11:19,447 --> 00:11:20,847
is at least a place to stay.

222
00:11:24,927 --> 00:11:25,687
Granny Gao.

223
00:11:26,207 --> 00:11:27,408
I heard

224
00:11:27,488 --> 00:11:28,408
that you're close with Ms. Zheng,

225
00:11:28,488 --> 00:11:29,368
who's injured.

226
00:11:33,687 --> 00:11:35,128
I'm Xu Lai, a reporter
from the TV station.

227
00:11:35,327 --> 00:11:36,327
I want to help Ms. Zheng.

228
00:11:37,408 --> 00:11:39,607
Can I ask you about the incident?

229
00:11:41,207 --> 00:11:42,008
Director Wang

230
00:11:42,207 --> 00:11:44,008
was talking nonsense.

231
00:11:45,567 --> 00:11:47,648
Zheng would never kill herself.

232
00:11:48,207 --> 00:11:49,168
Every day,

233
00:11:49,207 --> 00:11:50,327
she hopes that her son

234
00:11:50,528 --> 00:11:52,447
could visit her at the nursing home.

235
00:11:53,248 --> 00:11:55,927
So, the claim of her intention to set a fire

236
00:11:56,447 --> 00:11:57,327
doesn't exist at all?

237
00:12:07,008 --> 00:12:07,607
Director Wang.

238
00:12:08,447 --> 00:12:09,248
It's you again.

239
00:12:09,607 --> 00:12:10,528
I'm taking my wife
for a prenatal checkup.

240
00:12:10,648 --> 00:12:11,368
I don't have time for the interview.

241
00:12:11,967 --> 00:12:13,128
Can we talk about

242
00:12:13,288 --> 00:12:14,248
how you mistreated the elderly

243
00:12:14,447 --> 00:12:15,248
and created a false claim

244
00:12:15,408 --> 00:12:16,528
about Ms. Zheng's suicide?

245
00:12:23,447 --> 00:12:24,207
I warn you.

246
00:12:24,687 --> 00:12:25,847
Don't make baseless accusations
when you don't have the evidence.

247
00:12:26,087 --> 00:12:26,687
I do.

248
00:12:27,967 --> 00:12:29,447
Look at the materials used
for partitions.

249
00:12:30,008 --> 00:12:31,368
They are flammable.

250
00:12:33,447 --> 00:12:34,607
And the electrical cords
that are exposed to the air.

251
00:12:34,687 --> 00:12:35,288
Did you see that?

252
00:12:35,727 --> 00:12:37,528
Apparently, these are old and worn-out wiring

253
00:12:38,248 --> 00:12:39,648
with serious potential hazards.

254
00:12:41,927 --> 00:12:43,648
So, the fire in the nursing home

255
00:12:43,888 --> 00:12:45,447
is more likely to be initiated by these hazards.

256
00:12:48,248 --> 00:12:49,447
That's why Wang Yi

257
00:12:49,967 --> 00:12:51,248
put the blame on the elderly lady

258
00:12:51,687 --> 00:12:52,607
to divert attention.

259
00:12:55,447 --> 00:12:56,447
What do you want?

260
00:12:56,888 --> 00:12:57,967
I just want the truth.

261
00:12:58,528 --> 00:13:00,488
The truth is Ms. Zheng set on fire herself.

262
00:13:01,128 --> 00:13:02,207
But the firefighter who saved her said

263
00:13:02,408 --> 00:13:03,567
that she had a strong will to live.

264
00:13:03,888 --> 00:13:04,768
Because she can't walk well.

265
00:13:05,008 --> 00:13:05,727
She's useless.

266
00:13:06,607 --> 00:13:08,327
Do you have no responsibility at all?

267
00:13:08,807 --> 00:13:10,128
How did the fire start?

268
00:13:10,768 --> 00:13:11,768
Do you really want

269
00:13:11,847 --> 00:13:12,447
to push me so hard

270
00:13:12,528 --> 00:13:13,528
for someone who can't live much longer?

271
00:13:14,327 --> 00:13:15,408
Even without this fire,

272
00:13:15,607 --> 00:13:17,168
she has not much time left.

273
00:13:17,488 --> 00:13:17,888
Wait.

274
00:13:17,927 --> 00:13:19,288
You're the director of a nursing home.

275
00:13:19,888 --> 00:13:21,008
Is this your attitude
towards the elderly?

276
00:13:21,207 --> 00:13:22,327
What's wrong with my attitude?

277
00:13:23,008 --> 00:13:24,528
Her own son doesn't even care about her.

278
00:13:24,888 --> 00:13:27,327
We're kind enough to take her in.

279
00:13:27,847 --> 00:13:29,408
You better stop meddling.

280
00:13:29,447 --> 00:13:30,168
Okay?

281
00:13:30,488 --> 00:13:31,967
No one cares about the truth.

282
00:13:32,327 --> 00:13:34,327
The truth is that she wanted
to set on fire to commit suicide.

283
00:13:35,888 --> 00:13:37,687
These are all the potential hazards.

284
00:13:38,447 --> 00:13:39,288
I can only give you a definite answer

285
00:13:39,288 --> 00:13:40,648
